  .intro
    p Pennsylvania was the second state (commonwealth) to ratify the U.S. Constitution (just days after Delaware).
    p The General Assembly approved a first official flag in 1799, prominently featuring the Pennsylvania coat of arms. However, inconsistencies abounded so a few years later the flag was standardized to the version known today.
    p The flag was officially adopted June 13, 1907.

