  .guide
    .content
      h2 Construction
      p Pennsylvania statute specifies the dimensions of the flag in feet and inches. It should have a hoist of 4 feet, 6 inches and a fly of 6 feet, 2 inches.
      p This is an unusual 27:37 proportion, so the flag is usually produced with a proportion of 2:3.
      p It does not specify dimensions for the coat of arms beyond “proportionate size.”
      p The flag can also have knotted fringe of yellow silk, measuring 2 and 1/2 inches wide and a cord of white and blue silk, measuring 8 feet, 6 inches.
    .visual
